Few movies give me chills but this was one of them. Great choice in casting here as was a pleasant suprise. No one really annoyed me much. The MI6 Kingsman organization seemed as it should. 

A throwback to a bygone era perhaps.  But one which very well may be needed again today. 

Jackson fit the eccentric,  environmentalist, super geek nut case. Which i never much trusted any of those types anyways.  

Gazelle was clearly the best villain sidekick ever I think!!  She seemed to be the real brains behind the operation though. 

In the backgroud but clearly in control. An interesting character of which i would like to know more of a backstory on. 

Sofia Boutella i have known about for awhile now.  She is also in real life an extremly gifted dancer, and  performer. Who i didn't at first reconize until a friend pointed it out.  Great movie, casting and overall enjoyable film.  :b
